    <remarks>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>The Exception property is used to examine the exception without marking it as observed, whereas the <see cref="M:System.Threading.Tasks.UnobservedTaskExceptionEventArgs.SetObserved" /> method is used to mark the exception as observed. Marking the exception as observed prevents it from triggering exception escalation policy which, by default, terminates the process.</para>
    </remarks>
    <summary>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>Provides data for the event that is raised when a faulted <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task" />'s exception goes unobserved.</para>
    </summary>
